le=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 16, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fra1665702979044.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fra1665702979044.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fra1665702979044.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fra1665702979044\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Develop a Database Connector Incrementally\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">During connector development, you can integrate an incomplete DBMS connector with Uniface for testing purposes.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"fra1665702979044__context_w4006ab1b5b1_w4007ab1b5_w4008ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"fra1665702979044__topic_d62870e1_d62871e1_d62872e1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"fra1665702979044__note_w4009ab1b5b1b1b1_w4010ab1b5b1b1_w4011ab1b5b1_w4012ab1b5_w4013ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Uniface does not guarantee the correct operation of products integrated with an incomplete database connector.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fra1665702979044__p_d62873e1_d62874e1_d62875e1\">To develop a connector incrementally:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27443e1_d27444e1_d27445e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the Uniface installation program in the Uniface installation directory and select the user-defined connector. For more information, see the relevant information for your connector guide.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27446e1_d27447e1_d27448e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Uniface IDE, develop a test application with an entity in the database for which you are developing the connector.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27449e1_d27450e1_d27451e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Implement the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Info('I')</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Message ('M')</span>, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Logon ('L')</span> connector requests. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yla1665702916470.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yla1665702916470.html\" title=\"Provide Uniface with DBMS and connector characteristics, or supply logon information.\">Info ('I')</a> , <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dgv1665702916539.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dgv1665702916539.html\" title=\"Translate an error code to a text.\">Message ('M')</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hjv1665702916609.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hjv1665702916609.html\" title=\"Log on to the DBMS.\">Logon ('L')</a>.\n                  </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27452e1_d27453e1_d27454e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Define a connector error code for every connector function that is not implemented, as follows:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27455e1_d27456e1_d27457e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code> to the connector error code.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27458e1_d27459e1_d27460e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Return to Uniface with the return value for Exceptional error.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27461e1_d27462e1_d27463e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Compile the incomplete connector.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27464e1_d27465e1_d27466e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the test application with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pri</span> command line setting set to 255.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27467e1_d27468e1_d27469e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Attempt to enter, store, modify and retrieve data. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nqh1665702549702.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html\" title=\"Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the applicable message types.\">I/O Message Levels</a>.\n                  </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27470e1_d27471e1_d27472e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Observe the error messages in the message frame. If an error message appears for a connector request that is not implemented, the integration of the connector has been successful.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27473e1_d27474e1_d27475e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">After running the test application, implement the first connector function that returned an exceptional error.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27476e1_d27477e1_d27478e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Compile the connector.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fra1665702979044__li_d27479e1_d27480e1_d27481e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Repeat this procedure from the step 6, continuing the loop until you have successfully implemented all connector requests.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wgm1665702978828.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Integrate a User-Defined Database Connector with Uniface</a><p>Uniface allows you to define up to ten user-defined DBMS connectors, called UD0 through UD9, in every installation of Uniface or the Uniface Server.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527628\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527628\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Develop a Database Connector Incrementally Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Develop a Database Connector Incrementally During connector development, you can integrate an incomplete DBMS connector with Uniface for testing purposes. Note: Uniface does not guarantee the correct operation of products integrated with an incomplete database connector. To develop a connector incrementally: Run the Uniface installation program in the Uniface installation directory and select the user-defined connector. For more information, see the relevant information for your connector guide. In the Uniface IDE, develop a test application with an entity in the database for which you are developing the connector. Implement the Info('I') , Message ('M') , and Logon ('L') connector requests. For more information, see Info ('I') , Message ('M') and Logon ('L') . Define a connector error code for every connector function that is not implemented, as follows: Set uctrl->udrverr to the connector error code. Return to Uniface with the return value for Exceptional error. Compile the incomplete connector. Run the test application with the /pri command line setting set to 255. Attempt to enter, store, modify and retrieve data. For more information, see I/O Message Levels . Observe the error messages in the message frame. If an error message appears for a connector request that is not implemented, the integration of the connector has been successful. After running the test application, implement the first connector function that returned an exceptional error. Compile the connector. Repeat this procedure from the step 6, continuing the loop until you have successfully implemented all connector requests. Related Links Integrate a User-Defined Database Connector with Uniface Uniface allows you to define up to ten user-defined DBMS connectors, called UD0 through UD9, in every installation of Uniface or the Uniface Server. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}